07:16.940 --> 07:23.640
alien and have to deal with it in a life and death situation. The first of these episodes

07:23.640 --> 07:28.380
takes place from the crew lands on an alien planet and is discovered by a creature named Curl.

07:29.560 --> 07:35.260
Curl is a cat-like creature and he soon lures his way on board the ship. The scientists are very

07:35.260 --> 07:41.000
eager to study him and see what his physiological makeup is like and how his psychology has adapted

07:41.000 --> 07:47.220
into this type of planet and generally what he is. Elliot Groesfiner, the main character that ties

07:47.220 --> 07:56.000
the stories together, is somewhat suspect of Curl and his suspicions are well founded. In an

07:56.000 --> 08:03.440
accident they discover that Curl can control electrical energies through his body and once

08:03.440 --> 08:08.820
Curl discovers that the human beings have learned this from him, he becomes immediately very fearful

08:08.820 --> 08:15.900
of them. He's a very very powerful creature and they lock him inside a cage but he manages to

08:17.200 --> 08:23.400
negate the electronic lock and get out and starts horribly killing the crewman

08:24.100 --> 08:29.560
and then running back to the sail and locking him back inside it hoping to create a panic on board

08:29.560 --> 08:37.940
the ship. The crew almost immediately discovers what is happening and becomes a war between the

08:37.940 --> 08:47.240
crew and the creature and in the end Curl leaves the ship by means of a lifeboat because he doesn't

08:47.240 --> 08:52.620
understand the faster than light drive on the ship. He attempts to fly back toward his planet

08:53.400 --> 08:58.320
but he's traveling away from his planet faster than he is traveling toward it when he leaves the

08:58.320 --> 09:02.660
ship and even though he's flying toward his planet his planet still recedes into the distance

09:03.240 --> 09:10.960
and he goes insane trying to figure this out. The second episode in the book which is one of

09:10.960 --> 09:16.780
the original short stories is about a race of aliens that are very bird-like called the rim

09:16.780 --> 09:23.100
or the rim people. They have an entirely mental existence they communicate by telepathy and

09:23.400 --> 09:29.120
they try to contact the space beagle with their mental emanations through telepathy

09:29.620 --> 09:34.780
and they're friendly all they want to do is contact the ship but it creates havoc on the space beagle.

09:36.640 --> 09:42.520
This mental power that enters the spaceship drives some of them in mad it causes psychological

09:42.520 --> 09:48.020
aberrations it brings out hostilities it exaggerates certain mental conditions in the crew

09:49.980 --> 09:55.340
and Grossfiner the the same one who was suspicious of Curl in the previous episode is able

09:55.340 --> 10:03.480
with his specialized equipment to mentally contact the rim to let them know what's happening and

10:03.480 --> 10:07.740
ask them to call off their attack which is done and the space beagle is allowed to continue.

10:08.800 --> 10:15.560
The third section of the book deals with a somewhat different type of alien. The space

10:15.560 --> 10:22.980
beagle is voyaging between galaxies in intergalactic space where there is absolutely nothing when all

10:22.980 --> 10:29.460
of the sudden they come across the path of an alien who seems to be floating in this intergalactic

10:29.460 --> 10:37.160
void. The alien had no hope of ever reaching one of the galaxies he was stranded out there

10:37.580 --> 10:44.020
when this ship just happened to pass by and the alien immediately taps some of the energy from

10:44.020 --> 10:51.880
the drive of the ship and stops the ship dead in its tracks. The humans crawl out of the ship and

10:51.880 --> 10:58.860
fix the exterior and then they notice the alien floating right by the ship. The alien comes aboard

10:58.860 --> 11:06.740
the ship after they try to capture him in a cage and immediately recognizes the situation

11:07.900 --> 11:13.220
as being very advantageous to him. This creature is extremely powerful and he's from an ancient

11:13.220 --> 11:21.480
civilization that existed in the previous cycle of the universe. When that universe exploded this

11:21.480 --> 11:26.760
creature was shot out into the place where they found him without any hope of gaining access to a

11:26.760 --> 11:36.960
galaxy. When he meets the men he is able to use them as host creatures or bodies for his eggs

11:36.960 --> 11:44.680
in order to raise up more of these creatures. The Ixtel as the alien is called in the book

11:45.900 --> 11:52.860
takes over part of the ship and it's really a race between him and the rest of the humans

11:52.860 --> 11:59.120
as to who's going to control. If the humans allow him to gain the upper hand he will eventually

11:59.120 --> 12:04.820
control all of the galaxy that they're going to. The only way that the humans could rid themselves

12:04.820 --> 12:13.760
of Ixtel was by using their mental agility and leaving the ship long enough that they could

12:14.400 --> 12:19.340
impose a force field of energy that would kill the creature. The creature found out what they

12:19.340 --> 12:26.520
were doing just in time to escape and he got back into his original fix floating out in middle of

12:26.520 --> 12:33.460
intergalactic space with no hope of ever gaining access to the galaxy as the humans went on to

12:33.460 --> 12:40.500
their next episode. The last one involves the creature very difficult to describe it's sort of

12:40.500 --> 12:48.100
a cloud a huge cloud creature without any particular name but it feeds on death it started out as a

12:48.100 --> 12:55.660
very small small organism. First of all it fed on the deaths of insects then smaller animals and

12:55.660 --> 13:03.360
larger animals. It kept growing all the while and it's gotten so huge that it needs the the death

13:03.360 --> 13:09.740
of creatures on an entire planet to exist. So it's gained the power and the size and the strength

13:10.300 --> 13:15.320
to terraform planets and as the space people goes through a particular system they find that

13:15.860 --> 13:22.820
all of the planets they're passing are similar. They're covered with tropical vegetation with large

13:23.660 --> 13:29.000
primitive kinds of animals engaged in conflict which leads to to many deaths that this creature is

13:29.000 --> 13:35.500
feeding on. The scientists on the space beagle figure out what's happening and realize that their

13:35.500 --> 13:40.540
own solar system is in great danger because this creature is expanding all the time and they're

13:40.540 --> 13:44.980
afraid it's going to come to their own solar system. So they devise a plan whereby they

13:45.820 --> 13:51.920
they start destroying the planets that the creature is feeding on and lure him out into

13:52.860 --> 13:58.660
interstellar space where he is not allowed where he's not able to feed so that he is going to he

13:58.660 --> 14:05.340
will we know die away from the source of the death which nourishes him. So again through their cleverness

14:05.340 --> 14:11.060
through their ingenuity the the humans have triumphed over an alien which when you come right down to it

14:11.060 --> 14:15.960
is much more powerful than they are. And I believe that typifies a lot of the things in the novel in

14:15.960 --> 14:23.020
