14:23.320 --> 14:30.680
seem to outwit aliens that are much more powerful than they are physically and in some instances by

14:30.680 --> 14:38.180
specialized powers that they have. Curl could manipulate electromagnetic energies and Ixtel

14:38.180 --> 14:45.620
could move through solid matter but even with these abilities the humans by their own ingenuity

14:45.620 --> 14:50.260
could outwit their adversaries. I think we should say something for the aliens though.

14:51.020 --> 14:56.280
In most of the pulp novels of the time that this one was written we have so many of the bug-eyed

14:56.280 --> 15:02.940
monsters that are nothing more than monsters. Here we have aliens that are truly intelligent and

15:02.940 --> 15:10.160
are fighting the humans on a much greater level than just physical terror. They they're well thought

15:10.160 --> 15:17.780
out. They have purpose and a plan. We can say that these are really better aliens than what you

15:17.780 --> 15:23.700
would expect to find in most of the pulp novels of this time. I think that tradition that change in

15:23.700 --> 15:28.460
the way the bug-eyed monsters were were written about in science fiction came back in the 30s with

15:28.460 --> 15:34.480
Stanley Weinbaum, Martian Odyssey. Asimov is described that as the first science fiction story

15:34.480 --> 15:41.580
in which the aliens are not simply humans in a strange form. They have their own reasons for

15:41.580 --> 15:46.580
existing. They have their own ecology. They they belong to a particular planet and they're part of

15:46.580 --> 15:54.860
that planet. I think all of the aliens in this particular book are the realistic in terms of

15:54.860 --> 15:59.780
having an ecology built around them and having a psychology, a physiology which is not human.

